column5: Looking for a hut rental around keswick. One in which a few guys can stay the night. Want a weekend, All day Saturday, Sat night, All day Sunday. Let me know if anyone has anything. Not particular on which weekend. Anywhere basically from Keswick around to Barrie. We would be comming from Orangeville.  Thanks guys.  Curt  [emailÂ protected]
Curt   Not sure about Keswick side  but out of Gilford you have Terry Goy, or Ice cabins and in Lefroy  Love to Fish Simcoe and Lucky Sons.  rick
PM sent.  And welcome to the board, Curt.

Well looks like you guys need an ice -bungalow !!!!....man lake nipissing is famous for them you should check them out they have everything including satellite tv,bunk beds that you can lie in and still be jigging down the hole !!!! they all have gas BBQ's as well outside,man its like being in your living room,it would be something you would remember forever,i think there are some operators on simcoe that do the same thing,and lake nip,isnt to far its only a few hours from where you guys are,and the walleye fishing is usually good to great ,oh and lots of pike too !!! good-luck you should get lots of ideas if you google it for the lake nip area,or hut operators list,or try icefishingontario....
